9 PART IX. TRAUMA-INFORMED TRAINING PROGRAM
10 §1300.81. Definitions
11 As used in this Section, the following terms have the meaning ascribed to them:
12 (1) "Department" means the Louisiana Department of Health.
13 (2) "Adverse childhood events" or "ACEs" means potentially traumatic
14 events occurring before the age of eighteen, including but not limited to all of the
15 following:
16 (a) Physical, emotional, or sexual abuse.
17 (b) Physical or emotional neglect.
18 (c) Household substance abuse.
19 (d) domestic violence.
20 (e) Parental incarceration.
21 (f) Other forms of chronic stress or instability.
